<br>
I made a mage primarily because, having read the game manual and, knowing no-one who played, I wanted to play a class which could solo when needed, but which could still make a decent contribution to a group when needed.<br>
<br>
54 levels and just over a year later, I see no reason to regret my choice. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Despite what many posts on this board say (some of which I agree with, some of which I don't) I still feel that:-<br>
<br>
a) I made the right choice, and<br>
<br>
b) My mage is a hell of a lot of fun to play.<br>
<br>
So that's why I made a mage....<br>
<br>
Bariel<br>
54th Level Magician<br>
