I wanted the ability to have good nukes. At this time there was a big debate over mage and wizard nukes and how there was little difference in damage, making mage pets put them well over wizard damage ( this was a year and a half ago ). So at the time I thought I'd made an awesome decision. I pretty much solo'd to death. I can't tell you how many times I've given up on my mage, tired of the same old.<br>
But now, here I am, I pushed and pushed, and I'm proud to say I made it for level 49.<br>
In essence, why'd I pick it?<br>
I wanted to nuke well. But I didn't want that to be my only side to my character. I wanted to be diverse. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchopper2423.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chopper2423</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/01 4:09:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theotaku.com/dragonball/animated/gotenksfusion.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you  make a mage?</span><hr size=1> yea, none of those for me.<br>
