<br>
I actually didn't create the mage... I made a monk.  I was new to this whole system ... the RP i did was white wolf ... thus mage and vampire and werewolf.  I enjoyed the monk I played in a AD&amp;D game .. so I went with it.  Well after a while i got annoyed... I first started to experience the ding - unding phenomenon.  So I started a chanter, and had some fun with that.  Then one day my boyfriend created a mage for me, since his cousin has a blast with his... thus Iwka was born with probably all the right stats, cuz what did I know =)  <br>
<br>
I loved being a mage!  at that point i was more working alongside my pet ... like I always had a hunting partner.  and I thought that was great.  I could nuke and I had always a variety of pet types to choose from.  But as with all these characters i played around 12th lvl I just got discouraged and lost, and stopped playiing for a few months.<br>
<br>
I logged in one day to my mage, and just left Faydwer and wandered around.  I find random things to hunt, some random camps, and make some friends.  All of a sudden this game is fun again!  I get to 16, get new spells ... eventually get malise and decide this is the best spell ever lol... I just started having an absolute blast soloing, and occasionally grouping with friends.  <br>
<br>
So for me, the fact that i'll be able to summon beer in just one more yellow gem aside, there is not real reason that I play a mage except that it really is naturally the most fun class!  I can solo and group, and those who think mages aren't good in a group obviously have never grouped with me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We have pets for various situations with different abilities.  sure pathing sucks, and those who dont' control pets have given those who do a bad name, but we summon powerful allies in our pets.  I never have to buy food or water, or worry about getting my pet or my friends weapons, in tight situations i get my clerics and druids more mana even with than C2 and a wis buff, because those buffs obviously didn't cut it.  And another perk which I like is that I don't have to go roleplay because I don't rez, I don't port, and I don't cast chanter buffs.  I can deal with the people who need sight stones or bandaids, and luckily everyone always bothers the druids for powerlevelling =)  <br>
<br>
I'm glad that Iwka was created for me ... I probably wouldn't be playing EQ if it weren't for my mage.<br>
<br>
... now if only i could get out of 51 ...<br>
